HEADWORD: Bullfrog
<hw>Bull"frog`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A very large species of frog (<spn>Rana Catesbiana</spn>), found in
North America; -- so named from its loud bellowing in spring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

